Antibody titers for PCV2-infected pigs were also determined by an IPMA on PCV2-infected cells (Truong et al., 2001) to search for a possible correlation between the IPMA titer and the OD ratio. Endpoint IPMA titers of 35 sera collected at 2–6 weeks p.i. from PCV2-infected piglets were plotted against the OD ratio of the corresponding serum (Fig. 2
). The results show linear regression between the log10
 titer of IPMA and the OD ratio (Spearman’s correlation coefficient=0.84; P<0.0001) within a minimum and a maximum limited range, respectively, of 2 and 4.7 (IPMA), and 1.59 and 5.5 (OD ratio).
